metadata:

hadiths[6]{hadithnumber,arabic,bengali,english,french,indonesian,russian,urdu,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
{"hadithnumber": "2201", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ يُوسُفَ، أَخْبَرَنَا مَالِكٌ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنِ الأَعْرَجِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ ـ رضى الله عنه ـ أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَطْلُ الْغَنِيِّ ظُلْمٌ، فَإِذَا أُتْبِعَ أَحَدُكُمْ عَلَى مَلِيٍّ فَلْيَتْبَعْ ‏\"\"‏‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet (ﷺ) said, \"Procrastination (delay) in paying debts by a wealthy man is injustice. So, if your  debt is transferred from your debtor to a rich debtor, you should agree.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "Narrated Abu Huraira:", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
{"hadithnumber": "2202", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يُوسُفَ، حَدَّثَنَا سُفْيَانُ، عَنِ ابْنِ ذَكْوَانَ، عَنِ الأَعْرَجِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ ـ رضى الله عنه ـ عَنِ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَطْلُ الْغَنِيِّ ظُلْمٌ، وَمَنْ أُتْبِعَ عَلَى مَلِيٍّ فَلْيَتَّبِعْ ‏\"\"‏‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet (ﷺ) said, \"Procrastination (delay) in paying debts by a wealthy person is injustice. So, if your  debt is transferred from your debtor to a rich debtor, you should agree.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "Narrated Abu Huraira:", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
{"hadithnumber": "2203", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا الْمَكِّيُّ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ، حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ أَبِي عُبَيْدٍ، عَنْ سَلَمَةَ بْنِ الأَكْوَعِ ـ رضى الله عنه ـ قَالَ كُنَّا جُلُوسًا عِنْدَ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم إِذْ أُتِيَ بِجَنَازَةٍ، فَقَالُوا صَلِّ عَلَيْهَا‏.‏ فَقَالَ ‏\"‏ هَلْ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالُوا لاَ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ فَهَلْ تَرَكَ شَيْئًا ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالُوا لاَ‏.‏ فَصَلَّى عَلَيْهِ ثُمَّ أُتِيَ بِجَنَازَةٍ أُخْرَى، فَقَالُوا يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ، صَلِّ عَلَيْهَا‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ هَلْ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ ‏\"‏‏.‏ قِيلَ نَعَمْ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ فَهَلْ تَرَكَ شَيْئًا ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالُوا ثَلاَثَةَ دَنَانِيرَ‏.‏ فَصَلَّى عَلَيْهَا، ثُمَّ أُتِيَ بِالثَّالِثَةِ، فَقَالُوا صَلِّ عَلَيْهَا‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ هَلْ تَرَكَ شَيْئًا ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالُوا لاَ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ فَهَلْ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالُوا ثَلاَثَةُ دَنَانِيرَ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ صَلُّوا عَلَى صَاحِبِكُمْ ‏\"‏‏.‏ قَالَ أَبُو قَتَادَةَ صَلِّ عَلَيْهِ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ، وَعَلَىَّ دَيْنُهُ‏.‏ فَصَلَّى عَلَيْهِ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Once, while we were sitting in the company of Prophet, a dead man was  brought. The Prophet (ﷺ) was requested to lead the funeral prayer for the  deceased. He said, \"Is he in debt?\" The people replied in the  negative. He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\" They said, \"No.\" So, he  led his funeral prayer. Another dead man was brought and the people  said, \"O Allah's Messenger (ﷺ)! Lead his funeral prayer.\" The Prophet (ﷺ) said,  \"Is he in debt?\" They said, \"Yes.\" He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\"  They said, ''Three Dinars.\" So, he led the prayer. Then a third dead  man was brought and the people said (to the Prophet (ﷺ) ), Please lead his funeral prayer.\" He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\" They said, \"No.\"  He asked, \"Is he in debt?\" They said, (\"Yes! He has to pay) three  Diners.', He (refused to pray and) said, \"Then pray for your (dead)  companion.\" Abu Qatada said, \"O Allah's Messenger (ﷺ)! Lead his funeral  prayer, and I will pay his debt.\" So, he led the prayer.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوعبداللہ (امام بخاری رحمہ اللہ) نے کہا کہ مجھ سے ابراہیم نے کہا، انہیں ہشام نے خبر دی، انہوں نے کہ", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "2203", "narrator_chain": "Narrated Salama bin Al-Akwa:", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
{"hadithnumber": "2287", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ يُوسُفَ ، أَخْبَرَنَا مَالِكٌ ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ ، عَنِ الْأَعْر", "bengali": "", "english": "Narrated Abu Huraira:The Prophet (ﷺ) said, \"Procrastination (delay) in paying debts by a wealthy man is injustice. So, if your debt is transferred from your debtor to a rich debtor, you should agree", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ہم سے عبداللہ بن یوسف نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم کو امام مالک رحمہ اللہ نے خبر دی، انہیں ابوالزناد نے، ا", "grades": "", "reference": "Book 38, Hadith 1", "international_number": "2287", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
{"hadithnumber": "2288", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يُوسُفَ ، حَدَّثَنَا سُفْيَانُ ، عَنِ ابْنِ ذَكْوَانَ ، عَنِ الْأَعْرَجِ ،", "bengali": "", "english": "Narrated Abu Huraira:The Prophet (ﷺ) said, \"Procrastination (delay) in paying debts by a wealthy person is injustice. So, if your debt is transferred from your debtor to a rich debtor, you should agree", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ہم سے محمد بن یوسف نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے سفیان ثوری نے بیان کیا، ان سے ابن ذکوان نے، ان سے اعرج", "grades": "", "reference": "Book 38, Hadith 2", "international_number": "2288", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
{"hadithnumber": "2289", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا الْمَكِّيُّ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ ، حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ أَبِي عُبَيْدٍ ، عَنْ سَلَمَةَ بْ", "bengali": "", "english": "Narrated Salama bin Al-Akwa: Once, while we were sitting in the company of Prophet, a dead man was brought. The Prophet (ﷺ) was requested to lead the funeral prayer for the deceased. He said, \"Is he in debt?\" The people replied in the negative. He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\" They said, \"No.\" So, he led his funeral prayer. Another dead man was brought and the people said, \"O Allah's Messenger (ﷺ)! Lead his funeral prayer.\" The Prophet (ﷺ) said, \"Is he in debt?\" They said, \"Yes.\" He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\" They said, ''Three Dinars.\" So, he led the prayer. Then a third dead man was brought and the people said (to the Prophet (ﷺ) ), Please lead his funeral prayer.\" He said, \"Has he left any wealth?\" They said, \"No.\" He asked, \"Is he in debt?\" They said, (\"Yes! He has to pay) three Dinars.', He (refused to pray and) said, \"Then pray for your (dead) companion.\" Abu Qatada said, \"O Allah's Messenger (ﷺ)! Lead his funeral prayer, and I will pay his debt.\" So, he led the prayer", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ہم سے مکی بن ابراہیم نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے یزید بن ابی عبید نے بیان کیا، ان سے سلمہ بن اکوع رضی", "grades": "", "reference": "Book 38, Hadith 3", "international_number": "2289", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)"}
